    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.21/240.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Thomson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-02T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 31, 5 p.m. Department accepts Paragraph 2 of Article IV. Department’s
                    substitution of the word “advise” for the phrase “take the necessary steps” was
                    intended merely to indicate what the necessary steps meant. They could of course
                    only be advisory, and the Department agrees to “necessary steps” as heretofore
                    used in that sense.</p>
                <p>Department also accepts proposal of the Minister for Foreign Affairs for fifth
                    article, and hopes congratulations are not premature.</p>
                <p>We feel sure there will be no difficulty in securing despatch of duly accredited
                    agent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
